2.A — Footing & frost wall excavation
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Ground Level Contracting excavates strip footings, pad footings, and frost walls to structural tolerances for commercial and industrial projects in Barrie, Orillia, Innisfil, Wasaga Beach, and across Simcoe County. Spoil management, survey checks at critical lifts, and clear communication with your foundation trade keep forming lines true.

Cold-climate details — keyed joints, step footings, and insulation zones called for on drawings — are executed so your foundation contractor forms against correct lines and levels the first time. We coordinate with your surveyor and GC when benchmarks or grid offsets change mid-job.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2.B — Shoring, benching & deep excavations
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Deep cuts for parkades, mechanical levels, and utility corridors are staged with benching or with shoring coordinated to temporary works design. We maintain safe slopes and worker access while protecting adjacent structures, roads, and existing utilities — a recurring requirement on tight commercial lots in Barrie and Orillia.

Our crews align with structural engineers and site supers to sequence excavation, support installation, and backfill without compromising neighbouring foundations or public corridors. Documentation supports inspection and safety audits where the project demands it.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2.C — Elevator pits & loading docks
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Elevator pits and loading dock trenches require tight dimensional control, clean corners, and accurate sump and drain tie-ins for waterproofing and anchor placement. Ground Level Contracting excavates to manufacturer and structural tolerances for commercial cores, logistics facilities, and mixed-use builds throughout Simcoe County.

We coordinate sump locations, drain leads, slab ties, and penetration sleeves so vertical transportation and receiving areas meet structural and equipment specifications before concrete placement.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2.D — Site servicing trenches
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Storm, sanitary, and water runs are trenched to design grades with correct separation between parallel utilities and bedding that meets project specifications. Serving new builds and expansions in Innisfil, Wasaga Beach, Barrie, and Orillia, we protect existing services, keep trenches workable for inspection, and stage backfill to limit re-digging.

Our team sequences work with municipal or private connection requirements so tie-ins and inspections stay on your schedule.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2.E — Structural backfill & compaction
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Structural backfill around foundations and utilities uses engineered materials, moisture control, and lifts matched to geotechnical specifications. This scope protects slabs, pavements, and utilities from long-term settlement — a priority for commercial slabs and heavy-load yards in Simcoe County.

We coordinate proof rolling and density testing when specifications require verifiable compaction so your pavement and slab designs perform as intended.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2.F — Civil coordination with trades
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Civil excavation succeeds when dig windows align with forming, waterproofing, and underground mechanical scopes. Ground Level Contracting communicates penetrations, sleeves, tie-in locations, and hold points with your GC and trades to reduce idle crews and rework on commercial and industrial sites.

Clear sequencing keeps footings, trenches, and backfill moving in the order the structural and MEP packages require — especially on fast-track projects in Barrie, Orillia, and surrounding municipalities.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2.G — QA & documentation
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Consultants and owners often require traceability on civil scope: elevation records, trench photos, and as-built sketches suitable for turnover packages. We organize documentation so verification and warranty discussions move faster after substantial performance.

When third-party testing is specified, we stage lifts and exposure so density or proof tests occur without delaying the critical path.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2.H — Mass excavation & pad preparation
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Before footings and utilities, bulk cut-to-fill and pad preparation establish subgrade and platform levels for commercial shells, industrial additions, and phased developments. Ground Level Contracting executes mass excavation with attention to haul routes, spoils balance, and geotech-approved subgrade — supporting projects from Barrie and Orillia to Wasaga Beach, Innisfil, and rural Simcoe County.

We coordinate rough grading and pad certification with your survey and geotechnical consultants so structural excavation and building placement proceed on an approved surface.

