Q: Do you only excavate elevator and dock pits?
A: No. Ground Level Contracting delivers the full civil excavation package for commercial and industrial projects — footings, frost walls, deep cuts with benching or shoring, site servicing trenches, structural backfill, and mass pad work — so your foundation and underground scopes stay with one field partner across Barrie, Orillia, Innisfil, Wasaga Beach, and Simcoe County.

Q: Can you work directly from structural IFC drawings?
A: Yes. We build dig, trench, and backfill plans from the latest IFC issue, RFI responses, and geotechnical reports. When details change, we adjust benching, spoils handling, and sequencing so forming and mechanical trades are not left waiting.

Q: How do you manage inspection holds on deep trenches or structural backfill?
A: We coordinate inspection windows with your team, keep trenches safe and accessible for reviewers, and protect completed work so re-inspections are uncommon. When density or proof tests are specified, we stage lifts so testing fits the critical path.

Q: Do you provide documentation for consultants and owners?
A: Yes. We organize elevation records, photos, and as-built notes suitable for QA and turnover when your specification or contract requires traceability on civil excavation scope.

Q: What regions do you serve for commercial foundation excavation?
A: We mobilize for commercial and industrial civil excavation across Barrie, Orillia, Innisfil, Wasaga Beach, Midland, and Simcoe County — including projects that require coordination with municipal servicing and private site plans.

